rComments: she wasn't as awful as people say. she can be kind of confusing at times though. really appreciates student input. overall she's an average prof, not the best, but by far not the worst.

Extremely confusing prof. She's not familiar with the material herself and should not be even teaching this course. Has a hard time explaining when students ask for clarifications. Tests are also rather hard if you have no background in biology.

Very good examples, good teacher when she knows what she's talking about (which is most of the time). Eager to learn more about her subject and listens to constructive criticism (outside of class, obviously). Be prepared to take notes on the lecture slides, because they don't contain enough information for you to get by on their own.

A nice women, but a bad teacher. She doesn't do much to keep kids attention or make it interesting. It's kinda sad that a subjects that can be really kool is so boring. She pretty much told us she was gay. And props to her for being brave enough to say that (that can get to fired in some schools), but we really don't need to know, and don't care.
Good stories. Always willing to help.  Exams really hard - but fair. Fantastic prof.

She reads directly from the textbook, uses the examples in the textbook and when asked questions has a hard time clarifying.  Interesting material and is in her area of expertise, however when a nurse tells me she has no background in chemistry, i'm scared!! She says her exams are difficult from the beginning, not looking forward to the semester!
